 and social media have contributed to the movement's growth beyond the streets of Jerusalem into communities of former Christians around the world who now identify as the Children of Noah (Bnei Noah). She charts a path for future research while documenting the intimate effects of political theologies in motion and the birth of a new transnational Judaic faith.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aThird Temple movement, Temple Mount, Jewish theocracy, israel, politcs, zionism, rabbinic, judaism, religion, palestine, messiah.40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882820940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978828209423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978828209/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles